This paper focuses on the use of social media platforms for cyberattacks and disinformation campaigns during elections, which falls under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CR). The study also uses automated techniques to conduct spear phishing and disinformation campaigns, which could be classified under social media (cs.SI) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper examines the vulnerability of politically expressive Americans on Twitter, which could be relevant to the sub-categories of social networks (cs.SOC) and cybercrime (cs.CYBER).
